headline.main: FROM HAVANA.; ASSASSINATION OF THE BETRAYER OF LOPEZ. Public Excitement-Assault on the Police.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the arrival of the Black Warrior at New. Orleans we have the following letter from our regular correspondent: HAVANA, Sunday, Oct. 15, 1854. JOSE ANTONIO SANTOS CASTANEDA was born in Cuba, of Spanish parents,-was once sentenced to be shot by a Military Commission in Cuba, of which the late NARCISO LOPEZ was a member, and through whose aid and influence his life was saved, and himself and father freed from prison and ignooinious bonds.

docs.lead_paragraph: ITALIAN OPERA.--In consequence of the continued indisposition of Signor MARIO, there will be no opera to-night. It is, we hear, the intention of the management to produce immediately the Opera of "Semiramide." If the costumes and scenery are finished by Monday, there is a probability that this Opera will be given on that day. It is hoped Signor MARIO will then have entirely recovered his health.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the latest official report of the Registrar-General, the cholera was rapidly abating in London. The number of deaths in the last week of September was 754 against 2,050 in the first week of that month. The whole cholera mortality in London in September, was nearly 10,000.

headline.main: FOUR DAYS LATER FROM EUROPE; Cotton Unchanged--Consols 96 I-4 and 95 3-8. DEATH OF MARSHAL ST. ARNAUD. ARRWAL OF THE WASHINGTON. NOTHING OFFICIAL FROM SEBASTOPOL. Bombardment Commenced on the 5th of October.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Washington has arrived from Bremen, via Southampton. She brings 250 passengers, and London journals to the 11th inst. The Washington left Bremen on the 6th inst., and has 200 tons freight and the usual mails.
